1
00:00:01,810 --> 00:00:04,350
[Episode 31]

2
00:00:04,350 --> 00:00:08,340
Chief Jo.

3
00:00:08,340 --> 00:00:12,920
Let's call off our engagement.

4
00:00:12,920 --> 00:00:16,350
Excuse me?

5
00:00:16,380 --> 00:00:19,640
Break our engagement?

6
00:00:19,640 --> 00:00:22,680
Chairman!

7
00:00:22,680 --> 00:00:27,230
No matter the reason, I'm the one who's calling off the engagement,

8
00:00:27,230 --> 00:00:29,970
so I'll ask Lawyer Koh to arrange financial compensation.

9
00:00:29,970 --> 00:00:32,330
Why are you acting like this to me suddenly?

10
00:00:32,330 --> 00:00:34,530
What did I do wrong?

11
00:00:34,530 --> 00:00:36,740
You are the one at fault!

12
00:00:36,740 --> 00:00:40,630
Pushing your fiancée aside, you took Ms. Park to the vacation home.

13
00:00:40,630 --> 00:00:43,300
You spent the night with Ms. Park when the kids were there too,

14
00:00:43,300 --> 00:00:47,890
and now you want to cancel the engagement with innocent me?

15
00:00:47,890 --> 00:00:52,440
Chief Jo. I didn't call Ms. Park to come over.

16
00:00:52,440 --> 00:00:55,440
Se Chan called Ms. Park to bring his cell phone.

17
00:00:55,440 --> 00:00:57,990
The children set the storage on fire while playing in it,

18
00:00:57,990 --> 00:01:01,590
so Ms. Park got injured while saving them, so she stayed over with us.

19
00:01:01,590 --> 00:01:04,230
Are you expecting me to believe that story?

20
00:01:04,230 --> 00:01:07,560
Don't lie like that to me.

21
00:01:07,560 --> 00:01:10,070
Listening to you talking now,

22
00:01:10,070 --> 00:01:15,380
it's clear why I need to call off our engagement.

23
00:01:16,960 --> 00:01:20,890
Chairman, it's not like that...

24
00:01:20,890 --> 00:01:24,400
I really wanted to go to the vacation house with you and the children,

25
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:26,670
but Ms. Park was the one who went instead.

26
00:01:26,670 --> 00:01:31,770
So I got very upset and said such nonsensical things.

27
00:01:31,770 --> 00:01:35,720
But you don't understand my feelings.

28
00:01:35,720 --> 00:01:41,450
How can you be like this to me when I devoted myself to you and the children all this time?

29
00:01:41,450 --> 00:01:44,050
Have you devoted yourself to the children?

30
00:01:44,050 --> 00:01:46,750
Is that why you locked up my children in the dark storage?

31
00:01:46,750 --> 00:01:49,370
With what right!

32
00:01:49,370 --> 00:01:51,520
Pardon?

33
00:01:51,520 --> 00:01:54,980
- That was...
- That is enough reason

34
00:01:54,980 --> 00:01:59,340
to disqualify you from becoming my children's mother.

35
00:01:59,340 --> 00:02:01,120
I'm sorry, Chairman.

36
00:02:01,120 --> 00:02:05,880
I went overboard. I will apologize to the children and get along better with them.

37
00:02:05,880 --> 00:02:08,110
Even if the children did it wrong,

38
00:02:08,110 --> 00:02:13,870
you couldn't have acted that way if you had any affections for them.

39
00:02:13,870 --> 00:02:17,750
Chief Jo. Until now,

40
00:02:17,750 --> 00:02:23,310
though I have no feelings for you or the memory of the last three months,

41
00:02:23,310 --> 00:02:28,420
I tried to keep our engagement while waiting for the memory to come back.

42
00:02:28,420 --> 00:02:34,310
But there is no reason for that anymore. Let's end it here.

43
00:02:36,190 --> 00:02:40,110
Chairman. I'm sorry. I will not act like that again.

44
00:02:40,110 --> 00:02:43,450
Chairman, please.

45
00:02:43,450 --> 00:02:46,780
You are only making it harder for yourself.

46
00:03:11,560 --> 00:03:18,260
Acting like that to the Chairman's fiancée was wrong on my part.

47
00:03:18,260 --> 00:03:21,610
I deserved to be slapped.

48
00:03:21,610 --> 00:03:24,040
But what do I do now?

49
00:03:24,040 --> 00:03:27,940
How do I face Chief Jo every day from now on?

50
00:03:32,530 --> 00:03:35,320
Ms. Park. The Chairman just called.

51
00:03:35,320 --> 00:03:39,470
He wants you to take a week of sick leave and have a good rest.

52
00:03:39,470 --> 00:03:40,870
Sick leave?

53
00:03:40,870 --> 00:03:44,640
Yes. You need to rest from being injured while saving Se Jong and Se Chan.

54
00:03:44,640 --> 00:03:47,470
You haven't had a break all this time either.

55
00:03:47,470 --> 00:03:51,170
You should take advantage of it and visit your family and spend time with your friends.

56
00:03:51,170 --> 00:03:55,690
Don't worry about anything here. Rest well and come back.

57
00:03:55,690 --> 00:03:58,870
Yes, I will.

58
00:04:04,850 --> 00:04:08,200
- Dan Dan.
- Hey, Park Dan Dan.

59
00:04:08,200 --> 00:04:10,260
What's up with the bag?

60
00:04:10,260 --> 00:04:12,270
Did you get fired, Dan Dan?

61
00:04:12,270 --> 00:04:16,560
Or did you quit already to get ready to go to the US?

62
00:04:16,560 --> 00:04:19,400
No, it's not that. I got time off.

63
00:04:19,400 --> 00:04:23,510
Since I haven't had a break, the Chairman gave me a few days off.

64
00:04:23,510 --> 00:04:28,200
I see. It's no use quitting early. You have to make as much money as possible.

65
00:04:28,200 --> 00:04:29,750
You still have time.

66
00:04:29,750 --> 00:04:35,320
Dan Dan, what happened to your hand?

67
00:04:35,320 --> 00:04:38,670
This? I got a slight burn.

68
00:04:38,670 --> 00:04:40,880
While I was boiling water for coffee.

69
00:04:40,880 --> 00:04:42,230
It's nothing, Dad.

70
00:04:42,230 --> 00:04:46,380
Ah, honestly. You should have been careful.

71
00:04:46,380 --> 00:04:49,400
But, we are all leaving for work.

72
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:52,220
What are you going to do all by yourself?

73
00:04:52,220 --> 00:04:56,190
It's okay. I will stay home and rest.

74
00:04:56,190 --> 00:04:58,870
Right. If you are bored, come to the restaurant.

75
00:04:58,870 --> 00:05:04,210
If you get bored, come and wait tables, if you like.

76
00:05:04,210 --> 00:05:09,190
What are you saying to someone who's on a break? Don't you see the bandage on her hand?

77
00:05:09,190 --> 00:05:11,780
Right. She's here to take a break.

78
00:05:11,780 --> 00:05:17,640
Dan Dan, go to my room and sleep and rest.

79
00:05:17,640 --> 00:05:22,460
Yes, Grandma. I will rest a bit and go to the restaurant in a little while.

80
00:05:22,460 --> 00:05:24,310
No, no.

81
00:05:24,310 --> 00:05:26,200
You don't need to.

82
00:05:26,200 --> 00:05:28,570
Let's go then.

83
00:05:28,570 --> 00:05:31,250
Have a rest.

84
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:50,270
Is it you, Sarah?

85
00:05:50,270 --> 00:05:54,580
What's wrong with you?

86
00:05:54,580 --> 00:05:57,720
Hey, Sarah.

87
00:05:57,720 --> 00:06:00,380
Oh, my! Sarah!

88
00:06:00,380 --> 00:06:03,710
Hey, Sarah! What's going on? What happened?

89
00:06:03,710 --> 00:06:07,250
Why are you like this?

90
00:06:07,250 --> 00:06:13,690
Mom. What do I do now?

91
00:06:13,690 --> 00:06:19,150
My Se Jong... What should I do with my Se Jong now?

92
00:06:19,150 --> 00:06:22,990
Chairman wants to call off the engagement!

93
00:06:22,990 --> 00:06:26,810
What do I do now, Mom?

94
00:06:26,810 --> 00:06:29,940
Call off the engagement?

95
00:06:29,940 --> 00:06:35,430
Did his 22-year-old time's memory come back?

96
00:06:35,450 --> 00:06:37,390
No.

97
00:06:37,390 --> 00:06:40,760
His memory hasn't come back.

98
00:06:40,760 --> 00:06:43,970
But he says I'm not qualified to be his children's mom.

99
00:06:43,970 --> 00:06:47,980
He used that as an excuse to call off the engagement.

100
00:06:47,980 --> 00:06:49,590
What?

101
00:06:49,590 --> 00:06:51,940
What should I do now, Mom?

102
00:06:51,940 --> 00:06:56,800
Should I get a lawyer? This is very unfair, Mom!

103
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:59,780
After all this, he said, what?

104
00:06:59,780 --> 00:07:01,700
It's still an engagement.

105
00:07:01,700 --> 00:07:04,530
How can he do that overnight?

106
00:07:04,530 --> 00:07:06,760
That bastard...

107
00:07:06,760 --> 00:07:09,990
Hey, Wang Dae Ran!

108
00:07:09,990 --> 00:07:12,170
What are you going to do with my Sarah?

109
00:07:12,170 --> 00:07:14,310
What are you going to do now!

110
00:07:14,310 --> 00:07:19,560
What are you saying, Gi Ja? What is this all about?

111
00:07:19,560 --> 00:07:24,460
My daughter is on her death bed from the engagement getting canceled.

112
00:07:24,460 --> 00:07:26,800
Here you are, napping in the middle of the day!

113
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:28,680
Do you feel fine all yourself?

114
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:32,770
What? What do you mean the engagement got canceled?

115
00:07:32,790 --> 00:07:38,410
Did Young Gook's memory come back?

116
00:07:39,980 --> 00:07:42,730
His memory didn't come back.

117
00:07:42,730 --> 00:07:46,330
But he wants to cancel the engagement out of the blue.

118
00:07:46,330 --> 00:07:51,950
Why did he get engaged in the first place when he will call it off unilaterally?

119
00:07:51,950 --> 00:07:53,720
Hey, you, Wang Dae Ran.

120
00:07:53,720 --> 00:07:58,420
You take responsibility. Take responsibility for my Sarah!

121
00:07:58,420 --> 00:08:01,750
Madam, Madam! The Chairman is home.

122
00:08:01,750 --> 00:08:06,850
Is that so? That bastard is home.

123
00:08:08,410 --> 00:08:10,080
Where's Chairman Lee?

124
00:08:10,090 --> 00:08:13,570
- Hey, you! Come out!
- Please don't do this, Chief Jo's mother!

125
00:08:13,570 --> 00:08:15,630
- Driver Kang!
- Please stop, ma'am.

126
00:08:15,630 --> 00:08:17,160
Let me go.

127
00:08:17,160 --> 00:08:19,430
Let go of me!

128
00:08:19,430 --> 00:08:22,200
What's going on?

129
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:26,830
Please let go of her since she seems like she has something to say.

130
00:08:29,070 --> 00:08:33,550
My Sarah. What are you going to do about my Sarah?

131
00:08:33,550 --> 00:08:39,290
Everyone in the nation knows that you and my Sarah are engaged.

132
00:08:39,290 --> 00:08:44,230
You had all the fun taking her to an island and the vacation home.

133
00:08:44,230 --> 00:08:46,180
Why did you call off the engagement?

134
00:08:46,180 --> 00:08:48,550
Why did you get engaged with her if you were going to do this?

135
00:08:48,550 --> 00:08:51,620
How can you do this to her!

136
00:08:52,930 --> 00:08:54,570
I'm sorry.

137
00:08:54,570 --> 00:08:58,500
But I've talked to Chief Jo about this aplenty.

138
00:08:58,500 --> 00:09:01,230
I have nothing more to say about it.

139
00:09:01,230 --> 00:09:04,300
Driver Kang, please escort her out.

140
00:09:04,300 --> 00:09:06,280
- Hey!
- Please leave now.

141
00:09:06,280 --> 00:09:09,720
Hey, Chairman Lee, what?

142
00:09:09,720 --> 00:09:12,140
You have nothing more to say?

143
00:09:12,140 --> 00:09:14,620
When you ruined my Sarah's future like this?

144
00:09:14,620 --> 00:09:17,180
What makes you so arrogant?

145
00:09:17,180 --> 00:09:20,600
Hey, what's so great about you!

146
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:22,620
- Who do you think you are!
- Stop it, please!

147
00:09:22,620 --> 00:09:25,490
- Hey, you!
- Please, let's go!

148
00:09:25,490 --> 00:09:28,670
I will make you pay for this!

149
00:09:28,670 --> 00:09:32,890
What calamity is this when everything was fine until this morning?

150
00:09:32,890 --> 00:09:35,510
I don't think his memory has come back.

151
00:09:35,510 --> 00:09:39,750
What is Chief Jo going to do now?

152
00:09:44,020 --> 00:09:46,380
You bastard!

153
00:09:46,380 --> 00:09:48,920
This damn household...

154
00:09:48,920 --> 00:09:56,270
I've been feeling guilty and sorry about stealing money and gold bars.

155
00:09:56,270 --> 00:09:58,670
Not anymore.

156
00:09:58,670 --> 00:10:01,250
Let's call it even with this.

157
00:10:01,250 --> 00:10:06,070
It's even now!

158
00:10:09,060 --> 00:10:11,390
Ms. Park got time off?

159
00:10:11,390 --> 00:10:13,880
Yes, she's at home.

160
00:10:13,880 --> 00:10:18,620
Soo Chul, then let's invite Dan Dan too.

161
00:10:18,620 --> 00:10:22,330
What did I say? Did I call her Dan Dan?

162
00:10:22,330 --> 00:10:27,950
Perhaps I'm feeling very comfortable around her.

163
00:10:27,950 --> 00:10:31,920
He doesn't think that's strange, does he?

164
00:10:33,250 --> 00:10:34,670
Would that be okay?

165
00:10:34,670 --> 00:10:38,260
Of course. We need to talk about going to the US together.

166
00:10:38,260 --> 00:10:42,320
And listen to what she has in mind again as well.

167
00:10:42,320 --> 00:10:45,810
Okay, let's do that.

168
00:11:00,870 --> 00:11:03,230
Yes, CEO Anna.

169
00:11:04,900 --> 00:11:06,940
Now?

170
00:11:08,410 --> 00:11:10,030
Ms. Park, what happened to your hand?

171
00:11:10,030 --> 00:11:11,750
Did you get hurt?

172
00:11:11,750 --> 00:11:14,870
She burned it slightly while boiling water for coffee.

173
00:11:14,870 --> 00:11:18,750
You should have been careful. I hope it doesn't leave a scar.

174
00:11:18,750 --> 00:11:20,830
The doctor said not to worry.

175
00:11:20,830 --> 00:11:24,050
As long as I take the medication and put the ointment.

176
00:11:24,050 --> 00:11:27,050
That's fortunate.

177
00:11:27,050 --> 00:11:29,660
You must be hungry.

178
00:11:29,660 --> 00:11:31,890
Let's eat, Driver Park.

179
00:11:31,890 --> 00:11:34,450
Yes.

180
00:11:34,450 --> 00:11:35,570
Eat as much as you want.

181
00:11:35,570 --> 00:11:37,830
Please, start first.

182
00:11:48,730 --> 00:11:52,520
You are not eating much today, Ms. Park.

183
00:11:52,520 --> 00:11:55,460
I've eaten a lot.

184
00:11:55,460 --> 00:11:58,390
Everything tasted great.

185
00:12:01,900 --> 00:12:04,100
So, Ms. Park.

186
00:12:04,100 --> 00:12:08,810
Have you decided about going to the US?

187
00:12:08,810 --> 00:12:10,580
The US?

188
00:12:10,580 --> 00:12:16,230
We need to get a passport and apply for a visa.

189
00:12:16,230 --> 00:12:20,600
We are going together, right?

190
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:23,800
Well, about that...

191
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:29,660
I'm still thinking about it.

192
00:12:29,660 --> 00:12:34,810
Whether I should leave here,

193
00:12:34,810 --> 00:12:38,740
I don't know yet.

194
00:12:41,560 --> 00:12:46,620
- Ms. Park.
- What's wrong, Dan Dan?

195
00:12:46,620 --> 00:12:48,540
I'm sorry, CEO Anna.

196
00:12:48,540 --> 00:12:50,350
Please excuse me first.

197
00:12:50,350 --> 00:12:53,410
I'm sorry, Dad. I'll get going first.

198
00:12:53,410 --> 00:12:56,760
- Dan Dan.
- Ms. Park.

199
00:13:00,340 --> 00:13:04,520
I wonder why she's acting like that.

200
00:13:04,540 --> 00:13:08,560
I think it's because of her boyfriend.

201
00:13:08,560 --> 00:13:10,620
Pardon?

202
00:13:10,620 --> 00:13:12,770
A boyfriend?

203
00:13:12,770 --> 00:13:15,270
Does she have a boyfriend?

204
00:13:15,270 --> 00:13:20,300
Yes. I asked her if she had one when I stayed at Chairman Lee's house.

205
00:13:20,300 --> 00:13:22,740
And she said she had a boyfriend.

206
00:13:22,740 --> 00:13:25,780
Really? Who is it?

207
00:13:25,780 --> 00:13:28,300
She didn't tell me who he was.

208
00:13:28,300 --> 00:13:30,860
And later, when she came over to see me,

209
00:13:30,860 --> 00:13:35,410
she cried a river saying she had broken up with her boyfriend.

210
00:13:35,410 --> 00:13:38,740
My Dan Dan did so?

211
00:13:38,740 --> 00:13:42,560
I had no idea.

212
00:13:42,580 --> 00:13:47,110
I'm wondering if she's having issues with that boyfriend.

213
00:13:47,110 --> 00:13:52,760
It's just my hunch, but I wonder if the boyfriend is stopping her from going to the US.

214
00:13:52,760 --> 00:13:55,260
If not that, why would she act like that?

215
00:13:55,260 --> 00:14:00,010
It makes no sense for her to be like that over the Chairman's children.

216
00:14:00,010 --> 00:14:02,860
Right.

217
00:14:07,390 --> 00:14:09,690
- Ms. Park!
- Ms. Park!

218
00:14:09,690 --> 00:14:11,890
Ms. Park!

219
00:14:11,890 --> 00:14:15,560
Jenny, Se Chan, Se Jong. What are you doing here?

220
00:14:15,560 --> 00:14:18,150
We've come to visit you because you're on sick leave.

221
00:14:18,150 --> 00:14:19,990
Because I'm on sick leave?

222
00:14:19,990 --> 00:14:22,280
Here, it's a cake.

223
00:14:38,440 --> 00:14:40,590
Is it really that good?

224
00:14:40,590 --> 00:14:42,600
Yes. It's daebak delicious.

225
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:44,490
It's so good!

226
00:14:44,490 --> 00:14:47,990
Ms. Park, please make this for us at home, too.

227
00:14:47,990 --> 00:14:49,790
Okay, I will.

228
00:14:49,790 --> 00:14:55,210
But there are carrots Se Jong dislikes and spinach that Se Chan doesn't like.

229
00:14:55,210 --> 00:14:56,700
Is it still good?

230
00:14:56,700 --> 00:15:00,430
I know. I don't like the taste when it's a side dish.

231
00:15:00,430 --> 00:15:02,960
But they taste delicious like this.

232
00:15:02,960 --> 00:15:07,460
Me, too. Carrots don't taste like poop.

233
00:15:07,460 --> 00:15:13,310
Hey, Lee Se Jong, how can you talk about poop while eating?

234
00:15:28,430 --> 00:15:31,840
I'm so exhausted.

235
00:15:41,020 --> 00:15:43,680
Yes, Dae Beom, it's me.

236
00:15:43,680 --> 00:15:47,250
Are you feeling better, my baby Bambi?

237
00:15:47,250 --> 00:15:49,430
Have you been sleeping all this time?

238
00:15:49,430 --> 00:15:54,090
Yes, I rested a bit, and I feel better now.

239
00:15:54,090 --> 00:15:56,080
Don't come here to work anymore.

240
00:15:56,080 --> 00:16:00,330
I don't like seeing you having a hard time here.

241
00:16:00,330 --> 00:16:05,180
Let's find other ways to get my father's recognition.

242
00:16:05,180 --> 00:16:07,040
Okay, I got it.

243
00:16:07,040 --> 00:16:10,220
I will do as you say.

244
00:16:10,220 --> 00:16:12,010
Thank you, Se Ryun.

245
00:16:12,010 --> 00:16:15,280
- I'll call you when I'm done with work.
 - Okay.

246
00:16:15,280 --> 00:16:17,780
Kiss kiss?

247
00:16:21,850 --> 00:16:24,690
It's too difficult to get along with his family.

248
00:16:24,690 --> 00:16:27,580
What do I do?

249
00:16:29,880 --> 00:16:35,890
Is there no way to get Dae Beom out of there somehow?

250
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:44,850
Yes, Seung Ho.

251
00:16:44,850 --> 00:16:48,010
What? Golf?

252
00:17:12,340 --> 00:17:15,070
Nice shot!

253
00:17:15,070 --> 00:17:18,340
I'm playing well even though it's been a long time.

254
00:17:18,340 --> 00:17:20,150
I taught you how to golf.

255
00:17:20,150 --> 00:17:22,360
We went out golfing together.

256
00:17:22,360 --> 00:17:26,240
That's right. We did.

257
00:17:26,240 --> 00:17:29,410
It's been such a long time for me to come out like this.

258
00:17:29,410 --> 00:17:31,900
I feel refreshed and alive.

259
00:17:31,900 --> 00:17:33,840
It feels so liberating.

260
00:17:33,840 --> 00:17:35,090
Really?

261
00:17:35,090 --> 00:17:36,350
Let's come out often.

262
00:17:36,350 --> 00:17:38,520
Okay.

263
00:17:38,520 --> 00:17:41,730
It feels so great!

