Chairman?

768
00:53:06,670 --> 00:53:09,770
I wasn't trying to eavesdrop,

769
00:53:09,770 --> 00:53:12,370
but the conversation you had with Driver Park in front of the house,

770
00:53:12,370 --> 00:53:15,120
I overheard it accidentally.

771
00:53:15,120 --> 00:53:21,340
I had no idea that you had a hurtful past like that all this time.

772
00:53:23,380 --> 00:53:25,540
Ms. Park.

773
00:53:25,540 --> 00:53:28,920
On days like this, you have to lift up your mood by riding on a bicycle.

774
00:53:28,920 --> 00:53:30,910
The weather is a little cold,

775
00:53:30,910 --> 00:53:32,860
but let's ride this bicycle.

776
00:53:32,860 --> 00:53:37,580
I'll especially ride 100 laps for you.

777
00:53:37,580 --> 00:53:39,940
Get on.

778
00:53:42,940 --> 00:53:47,030
I said hurry up and get on!

779
00:53:47,030 --> 00:53:49,700
Quickly.

780
00:53:51,980 --> 00:53:56,040
♫ When I walk this road, ♫

781
00:53:56,040 --> 00:53:59,610
♫ it makes me cry  ♫

782
00:53:59,610 --> 00:54:01,320
♫ It reminds me of that person's touch ♫

783
00:54:01,320 --> 00:54:03,680
Hold on tight!

784
00:54:03,680 --> 00:54:07,690
Chairman... Just today,

785
00:54:07,690 --> 00:54:11,920
I'll lean on you like this just until today.

786
00:54:11,920 --> 00:54:14,620
Thank you so much.

787
00:54:14,620 --> 00:54:20,850
♫ My beautiful love ♫

788
00:54:20,850 --> 00:54:25,060
♫ It seems like ♫

789
00:54:25,060 --> 00:54:27,420
♫ love is bitter ♫

790
00:54:27,420 --> 00:54:29,360
I'll start peddling now.

791
00:54:29,360 --> 00:54:32,330
♫ The more I try to grasp it ♫

792
00:54:32,330 --> 00:54:35,550
♫ the further it gets ♫

793
00:54:35,550 --> 00:54:39,560
♫ Goodbye ♫

794
00:54:39,560 --> 00:54:43,160
♫ is easy ♫

795
00:54:43,160 --> 00:54:49,880
♫ My unforgettable love ♫

796
00:54:49,880 --> 00:54:53,410
♫ Why do you run away, love ♫

797
00:54:53,410 --> 00:54:57,690
♫ Like a shy child ♫

798
00:54:57,690 --> 00:55:01,500
♫ In case I lose it, ♫

799
00:55:01,500 --> 00:55:04,620
♫ I hold it tight ♫

800
00:55:04,620 --> 00:55:08,120
♫ But love always runs away ♫

801
00:55:08,120 --> 00:55:10,610
♫ chased by longing ♫

802
00:55:10,610 --> 00:55:13,760
I'll take my bag now, Chairman.

803
00:55:13,760 --> 00:55:19,960
♫ It would be nice to take a break ♫

804
00:55:19,960 --> 00:55:22,280
How are you, Ms. Park?

805
00:55:22,280 --> 00:55:26,330
Don't you feel a little better after riding on the bicycle?

806
00:55:26,330 --> 00:55:27,750
Yes.

807
00:55:27,750 --> 00:55:32,170
I feel a lot better thanks to you, Chairman.

808
00:55:34,180 --> 00:55:39,410
I'm just a private tutor who teaches your children.

809
00:55:39,410 --> 00:55:43,580
But thank you for treating me so warmly like this.

810
00:55:43,580 --> 00:55:48,080
I'll do my very best for the children during my remaining time.

811
00:55:48,080 --> 00:55:52,070
♫ I couldn't forget ♫

812
00:55:52,070 --> 00:55:55,630
♫ and buried in my heart ♫

813
00:55:55,630 --> 00:56:02,160
♫ My once precious love ♫

814
00:56:02,160 --> 00:56:06,890
♫ Why do you run away, love ♫

815
00:56:06,890 --> 00:56:10,380
I'm not leaving because you did something wrong.

816
00:56:10,380 --> 00:56:13,260
I just feel like I'm going to suffocate!

817
00:56:13,260 --> 00:56:15,620
This isn't living. It feels like a prison.

818
00:56:15,620 --> 00:56:19,930
It's like a dark cave where you can't see anything!

819
00:56:19,930 --> 00:56:24,830
What about me then? What about our Dan Dan?

820
00:56:24,830 --> 00:56:27,850
Just think that I'm dead.

821
00:56:31,360 --> 00:56:34,270
Wait, Dan Dan's dad!

822
00:56:35,880 --> 00:56:38,490
Dan Dan's dad!

823
00:56:38,490 --> 00:56:43,970
The two of us... Let's not die and raise the kids together.

824
00:56:43,970 --> 00:56:49,690
I'll be Dan Dan's mom.

825
00:56:49,690 --> 00:56:52,470
So don't do this.

826
00:56:54,520 --> 00:56:57,720
♫ Why do you run away, love ♫

827
00:56:57,720 --> 00:56:59,530
♫ Like a shy child ♫

828
00:56:59,530 --> 00:57:02,690
What possessed me...

829
00:57:02,690 --> 00:57:07,360
My precious family, who's been by my side until now...

830
00:57:07,360 --> 00:57:10,040
My wife...

831
00:57:10,040 --> 00:57:15,630
What in the world did I do to them?

832
00:57:15,630 --> 00:57:22,850
♫ It would be nice to take a break ♫

833
00:57:22,850 --> 00:57:28,410
♫ It would be nice to take a break ♫

834
00:57:28,410 --> 00:57:30,540
CEO?

835
00:57:30,540 --> 00:57:33,830
It's me.

836
00:57:33,860 --> 00:57:37,620
I'd like to meet you now for a moment.

837
00:57:59,370 --> 00:58:04,600
Soo Chul, you should just come in using the passcode from now. You know the password.

838
00:58:04,600 --> 00:58:06,380
I guess it's very cold outside.

839
00:58:06,380 --> 00:58:09,150
Hold on, Soo Chul. I'll hurry up and prepare a warm cup of tea for you.

840
00:58:09,150 --> 00:58:11,860
No, CEO.

841
00:58:11,860 --> 00:58:14,970
I don't need tea.

842
00:58:14,970 --> 00:58:18,280
I came because I had something to tell you.

843
00:58:18,280 --> 00:58:20,280
What is it?

844
00:58:20,280 --> 00:58:22,940
CEO...

845
00:58:22,940 --> 00:58:25,010
I'm sorry.

846
00:58:25,010 --> 00:58:27,110
I'm really sorry.

847
00:58:27,110 --> 00:58:30,990
I don't think I can go...

848
00:58:30,990 --> 00:58:33,760
to the US with you.

849
00:58:33,760 --> 00:58:36,540
No, I can't go.

850
00:58:36,540 --> 00:58:39,200
Soo Chul?

851
00:58:40,770 --> 00:58:44,160
What are you saying?

852
00:58:44,160 --> 00:58:48,200
I'm already looking into a house and a car for you.

853
00:58:48,200 --> 00:58:51,090
I'm sorry.

854
00:58:51,090 --> 00:58:56,040
I can never leave my family.

855
00:58:56,040 --> 00:58:58,130
But I got confused.

856
00:58:58,130 --> 00:59:01,940
I made a huge mistake.

857
00:59:01,940 --> 00:59:04,000
From now on, even if you're sick,

858
00:59:04,000 --> 00:59:07,200
I won't come here.

859
00:59:07,200 --> 00:59:10,250
Why are you suddenly doing this, Soo Chul?

860
00:59:10,250 --> 00:59:12,360
Thank you for everything until now.

861
00:59:12,360 --> 00:59:16,280
I won't forget your generosity.

862
00:59:16,280 --> 00:59:18,350
Goodbye.

863
00:59:18,350 --> 00:59:21,480
Soo Chul! Why are you doing this?

864
00:59:21,480 --> 00:59:25,740
Why are you doing this to me, Soo Chul? Did I make a mistake?

865
00:59:25,740 --> 00:59:28,770
Or did I do something wrong?

866
00:59:28,770 --> 00:59:32,470
Please don't do this, Soo Chul.

867
00:59:32,470 --> 00:59:34,690
No! That's not it.

868
00:59:34,690 --> 00:59:38,100
You didn't do anything wrong.

869
00:59:38,100 --> 00:59:39,670
No matter how tough it is,

870
00:59:39,670 --> 00:59:42,820
I need to stay here with my family.

871
00:59:42,820 --> 00:59:46,880
But I forgot my place and got in over my head.

872
00:59:46,880 --> 00:59:50,440
I committed a wrong that I shouldn't have!

873
00:59:50,440 --> 00:59:55,210
Please understand me.

874
00:59:55,210 --> 00:59:58,150
Soo Chul.

875
00:59:58,160 --> 01:00:01,000
Please think about it one more time.

876
01:00:01,000 --> 01:00:03,850
If you go like this,

877
01:00:03,850 --> 01:00:07,250
what am I going to do by myself?

878
01:00:11,820 --> 01:00:14,000
I'm sorry.

879
01:00:14,000 --> 01:00:16,660
Goodbye.

880
01:00:27,620 --> 01:00:30,950
Why is he suddenly being like that?

881
01:00:30,950 --> 01:00:34,450
How can he do this to me?

882
01:00:42,790 --> 01:00:46,280
I'm going to do whatever it takes

883
01:00:46,280 --> 01:00:49,730
to bring my Dan Dan and Soo Chul to the US.

884
01:00:49,730 --> 01:00:52,130
I'll do whatever it takes.

885
01:00:52,130 --> 01:00:55,700
I'll make sure we go together.

886
01:00:55,700 --> 01:00:57,940
My Dan Dan...

887
01:01:00,400 --> 01:01:02,690
I'm back.

888
01:01:02,690 --> 01:01:05,070
Ms. Park! When did you get here?

889
01:01:05,070 --> 01:01:06,660
Your vacation isn't over yet.

890
01:01:06,660 --> 01:01:10,240
Yes. But I just came back because I was worried about the children.

891
01:01:10,240 --> 01:01:14,880
I'm saying hello now because I got back so late last night.

892
01:01:14,880 --> 01:01:19,690
Oh, my goodness! How infuriating!

893
01:01:23,000 --> 01:01:25,860
Nothing happened, right?

894
01:01:25,860 --> 01:01:29,110
On the contrary, something huge happened.

895
01:01:29,110 --> 01:01:34,800
"Something huge?" What happened?

896
01:01:34,800 --> 01:01:36,770
Ms. Park.

897
01:01:36,770 --> 01:01:40,730
Chairman called off the engagement.

898
01:01:40,730 --> 01:01:44,860
What? Did he call off the engagement?

899
01:01:44,860 --> 01:01:47,670
Did Chairman do it?

900
01:01:51,520 --> 01:01:55,790
What? My husband said he wouldn't go to the US?

901
01:01:55,790 --> 01:02:00,090
That's right. He suddenly said he couldn't go.

902
01:02:00,090 --> 01:02:05,410
I'm also very confused now, honestly.

903
01:02:05,410 --> 01:02:10,020
Is there a problem that's stopping Driver Park from going to the US?

904
01:02:10,020 --> 01:02:14,220
Oh, no! Not at all. There's absolutely no problem.

905
01:02:14,220 --> 01:02:17,730
Oh, gosh. Is he crazy? Why is he suddenly saying he won't go to the US?

906
01:02:17,730 --> 01:02:21,420
I'll raise his salary to 200,000 dollars then.

907
01:02:21,420 --> 01:02:24,710
I just ask that you'll persuade him for me.

908
01:02:24,710 --> 01:02:28,010
T-Two hundred thousand dollars?

909
01:02:28,010 --> 01:02:29,780
Are you serious?

910
01:02:29,780 --> 01:02:31,920
- Yes.
- Oh, then...

911
01:02:31,920 --> 01:02:38,170
Will you still provide the house and a car you promised on top of that?

912
01:02:38,170 --> 01:02:41,600
Yes, of course.

913
01:02:41,600 --> 01:02:47,190
If I knew the reason why he couldn't go to the US, I would compensate him accordingly.

914
01:02:47,190 --> 01:02:52,560
But since I don't know the reason, I thought it might be because of his salary.

915
01:02:52,560 --> 01:02:57,840
The truth is, if I have to hire someone else instead of Driver Park, I'll need to invest that much more time,

916
01:02:57,840 --> 01:03:03,530
and there's no guarantee that I'll meet someone as diligently and trustworthy as him either.

917
01:03:03,530 --> 01:03:05,750
That's why I'm doing this.

918
01:03:05,750 --> 01:03:07,360
Oh, yes. I understand.

919
01:03:07,360 --> 01:03:09,470
I'll do my best to persuade him.

920
01:03:09,470 --> 01:03:11,970
Don't hire anyone else until then.

921
01:03:11,970 --> 01:03:14,170
My Soo Chul will go for sure!

922
01:03:14,170 --> 01:03:18,560
Don't you worry, CEO!

923
01:03:18,560 --> 01:03:21,920
Okay. I'm counting on you.

924
01:03:23,990 --> 01:03:25,810
What?

925
01:03:25,810 --> 01:03:27,840
200,000 dollars?

926
01:03:27,840 --> 01:03:32,250
Yes. It's over 230 million won with the exchange rates from today.

927
01:03:32,250 --> 01:03:36,270
He'll also get a house and a car as originally planned.

928
01:03:36,270 --> 01:03:42,440
How can his salary blow up to double like that?

929
01:03:42,440 --> 01:03:44,910
Is this all true, Aunt?

930
01:03:44,910 --> 01:03:49,350
Why are you even asking? She's so excited she's spitting as she talks.

931
01:03:49,350 --> 01:03:53,760
An annual salary of 200,000 dollars is at the level of what board members from big companies get.

932
01:03:53,760 --> 01:03:56,600
My Older-brother-in-law is amazing!

933
01:03:56,600 --> 01:04:02,660
Hold on a minute. What if he said he wouldn't go so that she'll raise his pay?

934
01:04:02,660 --> 01:04:06,270
- My father isn't someone who conjures up tricks like that.
- That's true.

935
01:04:06,270 --> 01:04:10,460
But the salary is way too high for him to say he won't go.

936
01:04:10,460 --> 01:04:11,830
- Honey!
- Oh!

937
01:04:11,830 --> 01:04:13,100
Older-brother-in-law!

938
01:04:13,100 --> 01:04:16,150
What is it? You said it was urgent.

939
01:04:18,640 --> 01:04:21,730
What's up with you all? Did something happen?

940
01:04:21,730 --> 01:04:23,520
Well...

941
01:04:23,520 --> 01:04:29,290
Honey! Did you tell CEO Anna that you won't go to the US?

942
01:04:29,290 --> 01:04:31,180
Did you go there again?

943
01:04:31,180 --> 01:04:35,570
I didn't go there. CEO Anna came to see me instead!

944
01:04:35,570 --> 01:04:40,720
She said she'll raise your salary to 200,000 dollars!

945
01:04:40,720 --> 01:04:48,570
Did you maybe say you wouldn't go so that she'll raise your salary? Was that it?

946
01:04:48,570 --> 01:04:52,940
If CEO Anna asks you to meet, don't meet her from now on.

947
01:04:52,940 --> 01:04:56,600
Also, I'm not going to the US. That's final.

948
01:04:56,600 --> 01:04:59,070
What?

949
01:04:59,070 --> 01:05:02,500
Why won't you go? She's saying she'll double your salary!

950
01:05:02,500 --> 01:05:07,400
It's not as if you'll be doing physical labor, like carrying bricks on your back.

951
01:05:07,400 --> 01:05:12,150
It's a comfortable job where you only need to drive her around and manage money. What's the issue?

952
01:05:12,150 --> 01:05:16,970
There are even men who go to the desert in the Middle East to work!

953
01:05:16,970 --> 01:05:19,620
Stop it, Honey.

954
01:05:19,620 --> 01:05:23,280
I'm just going to focus on the chicken restaurant here.

955
01:05:23,280 --> 01:05:27,640
Don't tell me to go to the US anymore, all right?

956
01:05:27,640 --> 01:05:30,570
Oh, gosh.

957
01:05:30,570 --> 01:05:36,510
Hey, Geon! What's wrong with him?

958
01:05:36,510 --> 01:05:40,700
Am I the weird one, or is it him?

959
01:05:40,700 --> 01:05:43,910
His salary will be 200,000 dollars!

960
01:05:43,910 --> 01:05:46,500
It's over 230 million in Korean money!

961
01:05:46,500 --> 01:05:50,640
Why is he saying he won't take it?

962
01:05:50,640 --> 01:05:59,260
You're right. I also don't think it's smart for him to turn down such an amazing offer.

963
01:05:59,260 --> 01:06:01,550
It's absurd!

964
01:06:01,550 --> 01:06:06,060
Seriously, why wouldn't he?

965
01:06:14,680 --> 01:06:21,570
CEO Anna... Why are you going this far?

966
01:06:21,570 --> 01:06:24,790
I'm not worth that much.

967
01:06:42,250 --> 01:06:45,850
Soo Chul.

968
01:06:45,850 --> 01:06:47,810
Take a seat first.

969
01:06:47,810 --> 01:06:54,260
CEO. I clearly explained to you that I couldn't go to the US.

970
01:06:54,260 --> 01:06:58,660
But why did you see my wife again and say strange things?

971
01:06:58,660 --> 01:07:01,810
Why are you confusing my family?

972
01:07:01,810 --> 01:07:05,850
That's because you suddenly said you couldn't go to the US with me.

973
01:07:05,850 --> 01:07:11,900
Is that why you met my wife and talked about money?

974
01:07:11,900 --> 01:07:16,110
Me doing that shows you mean that much to me.

975
01:07:16,110 --> 01:07:22,050
If your feelings for me were true, at the very least,

976
01:07:22,050 --> 01:07:26,160
you shouldn't play with my family's feelings with money like that.

977
01:07:26,160 --> 01:07:32,000
Are you saying that you'll buy my heart with money?

978
01:07:32,000 --> 01:07:35,240
I'm disappointed.

979
01:07:35,240 --> 01:07:37,470
No, Soo Chul. That's not what I meant.

980
01:07:37,470 --> 01:07:45,600
I did it because I wanted to go to the US with you and Ms. Park. I made a mistake.

981
01:07:45,600 --> 01:07:48,250
I'm sorry.

982
01:07:48,250 --> 01:07:50,830
I understand where you're coming from.

983
01:07:50,830 --> 01:07:58,010
So why don't you take a seat and talk about it over tea with me?

984
01:08:30,230 --> 01:08:34,670
Isn't this Zucchini Kimchi soup?

985
01:08:34,670 --> 01:08:36,680
Yes, that's right.

986
01:08:36,680 --> 01:08:38,690
This is my mom's specialty.

987
01:08:38,690 --> 01:08:41,350
Other people don't really know this Zucchini Kimchi soup.

988
01:08:41,350 --> 01:08:46,840
I once missed the bus because I liked this rest stop udon so much.

989
01:08:46,840 --> 01:08:48,270
Are you CEO Kim?

990
01:08:48,270 --> 01:08:51,720
Yes, that's right. I'm Anna...

991
01:08:53,580 --> 01:08:55,660
CEO!

992
01:09:08,490 --> 01:09:14,570
Who are you? What's your true identity?

993
01:09:14,570 --> 01:09:17,380
Who are you!

994
01:09:41,160 --> 01:09:48,540
♫ Please be my strength ♫

995
01:09:48,540 --> 01:09:55,890
♫ So I can find the way that's given to me ♫

996
01:09:55,890 --> 01:10:03,280
♫ Please open a way for me ♫

997
01:10:03,280 --> 01:10:10,500
♫ The hidden road of mine ♫

998
01:10:17,610 --> 01:10:20,640
[Young Lady and Gentleman]

999
01:10:20,640 --> 01:10:24,490
- You came to see me because you were worried about me, right? It's all so obvious!
- That's not it.

1000
01:10:24,490 --> 01:10:26,580
- Let me check just once!
- I told you, that's not it!

1001
01:10:26,580 --> 01:10:28,820
- Just once!
- I'm telling you, it's not!

1002
01:10:28,820 --> 01:10:31,840
Thank you, Seung Ho. I had a lot of fun today, thanks to you.

1003
01:10:31,840 --> 01:10:33,610
- What did you do today?
- I was home.

1004
01:10:33,610 --> 01:10:35,340
I saw you get off from a guy's car just now.

1005
01:10:35,340 --> 01:10:38,460
Why did you trick me? I'm offended.

1006
01:10:38,460 --> 01:10:41,920
- The children will figure out if you're acting like this.
- Are you upset with our dad or something?

1007
01:10:41,920 --> 01:10:43,410
Please be careful in front of the children.

1008
01:10:43,410 --> 01:10:46,190
How about starting it over with me again, Chief Jo?

1009
01:10:46,190 --> 01:10:49,330
You dare to think you can date me because my fiancé dumped me?

1010
01:10:49,330 --> 01:10:51,390
How dare you hit on me!

1011
01:10:51,390 --> 01:10:53,560
This is our Dan Dan. Our Dan Dan!

1012
01:10:53,560 --> 01:10:55,540
Why is my Dan Dan's photo here?

1013
01:10:55,540 --> 01:10:57,160
Ji Young!

1014
01:10:57,160 --> 01:10:59,930
You... You are Ji Young.

1015
01:10:59,930 --> 01:11:04,070
Kim Ji Young!
